# Panel, Canvas and Preview Windows
#
:Panel:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
Panel

The Icon Editor panel contains:

o  The File, View, Edit, and Properties menus
o  The Palette button
o  Eight drawing options
o  Nine fill choices and an outline for drawing
   squares, circles, or ellipses
o  Arrows for moving the icon or a selected 
   region in one-pixel increments
o  The flip tools
o  The rotate tools

For help on a specific panel item, move the
pointer over that item and press the Help key on
your keyboard.

#
:Canvas:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
Canvas

The canvas shows a magnified version of your icon.
Each pixel is represented by a square of 7-by-7 
pixels.  

Click MENU on the canvas to display an Edit menu.

The square at the top right of the Icon Editor
window displays the icon in its actual size.

