# 	File Menu
:FileButton:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
File

Provides options to open, save, and print files:

Load	For choosing the file you want to open.

Save	For saving the current icon to the 
	previously opened file.

Save As	For saving the current icon and specifying
	a folder, file name, and format.

Print	For specifying the settings that control
	printing.

#
:LoadMenuItem:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
Load

Displays a window from which you choose the file
for the icon you want to open.

Keyboard shortcut:  Meta-O

#
:SaveMenuItem:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
Save

Saves your current icon in the currently opened
file.

If your icon has not yet been saved, or you want 
to save it in a different format, use Save As.

Keyboard shortcut:  Meta-S

#
:SaveAsMenuItem:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
