# 	Edit Menu
:EditButton:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
Edit

Choose from these options:

Undo	Undoes up to seven of your last drawing
	or editing actions.

Redo	Restores your drawing to the state it was
	in before you chose Undo.

Clear	Clears the canvas.

Cut	Removes the entire icon or a selected
	region and places it on a clipboard.

Copy	Copies the entire icon or a selected
	region and places it on a clipboard.  

Paste	Pastes the contents of the clipboard in a
	region you define.

Invert	Makes black pixels white and white pixels
	black in the entire icon or selected 
	region.


:UndoMenuItem:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
Undo

Undoes up to seven of your last drawing or
editing actions.

You can use Redo to restore something you
have undone.

Keyboard shortcut:  Meta-Z

#
:RedoMenuItem:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
Redo

Restores your drawing to the state it was in
before you chose Undo.

You can redo up to seven actions.

Keyboard shortcut:  Shift Meta-Z

#
:ClearMenuItem:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
Clear

Clears the canvas.

If you want the drawing back, choose Undo.

#
:CutMenuItem:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
Cut

Removes the entire icon or a selected region
and places it on a clipboard.

You can then paste whatever you cut.

Keyboard shortcut: Meta-X

#
:CopyMenuItem:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
Copy

Copies the entire icon or a selected region
and places it on a clipboard.

(Copy leaves the original intact.)

You can then paste whatever you copied.

Keyboard shortcut:  Meta-C

#
:PasteMenuItem:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
Paste

Pastes the contents of the clipboard in a
region you define.

To use Paste:

1.  Choose Region for the drawing mode.
2.  Drag SELECT to define the region, which
    appears as a dashed line.
3.  Choose Paste from the Edit menu.

Keyboard shortcut:  Meta-V

#
:InvertMenuItem:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
Invert

Makes black pixels white and white pixels black
in the entire icon or selected region.

