:BrushSetting:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
Drawing Options

Eight options for what the pointer will draw
on the canvas.

Click SELECT on any of the drawing options to
choose it.

Option		What it does
________________________________________________

Point		When you click SELECT on the
		canvas, one black pixel is
		inserted at the hot spot (tip) 
		of the pointer.

		When you point to a black or
		color pixel and click ADJUST,
		the pixel turns white.

Line		Draws a line 1-pixel wide when
		you drag SELECT.

Square		Draws open or filled squares or
		rectangles, using any fill
		pattern.

		Drag SELECT from one corner to the
		opposite corner to draw a square.

Circle		Draws open or filled circles, 
		using any fill pattern.

		Drag SELECT from the center of the
		circle to its outside. 

Ellipse		Draws open or filled ellipses, 
		using any fill pattern.

		Drag SELECT from the center of the
		ellipse to its outside. 

Text		Displays a Text window. Choose the
		options you want, type the text in
		the Text window, then insert it 
		into the icon by moving the 
		pointer onto the canvas and
		clicking SELECT.

Region		Defines a rectangular region on
		the canvas.

		Drag SELECT to define the region.
		You can then move, flip, or 
		rotate it by clicking on any of
		the Move buttons.

		You can also cut, copy, and
		paste regions.

Erase		Erases pixels on the canvas.

		Drag SELECT to erase the pixel
		under the front tip of the eraser.

