:FillSetting:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
Fill Choices

Nine patterns or an outline for drawing squares,
circles, or ellipses.

Click SELECT on any of the fill choices to
select it.

These choices are available only when the draw
option is one of those fillable shapes. The open 
square draws an outline of the shape, using a line
1-pixel wide.

:ColorToggle:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/iconedit.handbook
Color/B&W

Determines whether your icon is in color or black
and white. If you have a black and white system,
you can't choose color.

Click SELECT on the option you want.

If you change your icon from color to black and
white, you lose the colors--even if you switch
back. Choose Undo from the Edit menu to restore
the colors.

